<paragraph blockId="2.[151,1437,293,426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[151,271,293,318]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">Definition</emphasis>
. Massive shallow cup shaped maroon brown lithistids that discolour ethanol into a purplish brown colour. Ectosomal megascleres are smooth ectosomal 
<taxonomicName box="[761,913,329,354]" class="Demospongiae" family="Corallistidae" genus="Isabella" kingdom="Animalia" order="'lithistida'" pageId="2" pageNumber="435" phylum="Porifera" rank="species" species="dichotriaenes">dichotriaenes</taxonomicName>
, occasional triaenes, one to two 
<typeStatus box="[1282,1341,330,354]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">types</typeStatus>
of large oxeas and dicranoclone desmas, microscleres are a combination of centrotylote microacanthoxeas, smooth microxeas, spirasters and streptasters (modified from 
<bibRefCitation author="Schlacher-Hoenlinger" box="[752,1123,401,426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435" refString="Schlacher-Hoenlinger, M. A., Pisera, A. &amp; Hooper, J. N. A. (2005) Deep-sea &quot; lithistid &quot; assemblages from the Norfolk Ridge (New Caledonia), with description of seven new species and a new genus (Porifera, Demospongiae). Zoosystema, 27 (4), 649 - 698." type="journal article" year="2005">
Schlacher-Hoenlinger 
<emphasis box="[1004,1060,401,425]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="435">et al.</emphasis>
<number box="[1067,1123,401,426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435" value="2005.0">2005</number>
</bibRefCitation>
and 
<bibRefCitation author="Carvalho" box="[1177,1411,401,426]" pageId="2" pageNumber="435" refString="Carvalho, F. C., Pomponi, S. A. &amp; Xavier, J. R. (2015) Lithistid sponges of the upper bathyal of Madeira, Selvagens and Canary Islands, with description of a new species of Isabella. Journal of the Marine Biological Association of the United Kingdom, 95 (7), 1287 - 1296. http: // dx. doi. org / 10.1017 / S 0025315414001179" type="journal article" year="2015">
